120 grams Bulgur Wheat
20 grams Chicken Stock Paste
240 grams British Beef Mince
1 sachet(s) Curry Powder Mix
50 grams Rogan Josh Curry Paste
1 carton(s) Tomato Passata
120 grams Peas
75 grams Greek Style Natural Yoghurt
220 milliliter(s) Water for the Bulgur
50 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce
1 tbsp Honey

Pour the water for the bulgur (see pantry) into a large saucepan, stir in half of the chicken stock paste and bring to the boil.
Stir in the bulgur, bring back up to the boil and simmer for 1 min.
Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for 12-15 mins or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a frying pan on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the beef mince, 5-6 mins. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.
Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the curry powder. Fry for 1 min more.
Stir in the rogan josh curry paste, passata, water for the sauce (see pantry) and the remaining chicken stock paste.
Bring up to a boil, then lower to a simmer.
Stir through the peas and cook for 2-3 mins.

Fluff up the bulgur and share between bowls.
Stir the honey (see pantry) into the beef.
Top with your beef rogan josh.
Dollop over your yoghurt.
Enjoy!